    "title": "Lead Instructional Designer at Narayana Group",
    "description": "Join the Narayana Group family as a Instructional Designer in Gurgaon. We believe in empowering our employees with the tools, training, and environment they need to succeed.\n\nAbout Narayana Group:\nNarayana Group is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Coordinate with academic counselors for student career guidance\n• Maintain classroom discipline and create a positive learning environment\n• Develop and deliver engaging lesson plans for students\n• Contribute to school newsletter, blogs, and other publications\n• Maintain student records and prepare progress reports\n• Utilize technology and digital tools to enhance learning outcomes\n• Participate in school events, workshops, and training programs\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• CA / CMA / CFA certification\n• 10-15 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Student Assessment\n• Proficiency in Classroom Management\n• Proficiency in Bloom's Taxonomy\n• Proficiency in Special Education\n• Proficiency in Educational Technology\n• Proficiency in Pedagogy\n• Proficiency in Communication Skills\n• Proficiency in E-learning\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Referral bonus program\n• Flexible working hours\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Salary Range: 20 LPA - 40 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Gurgaon, Haryana, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Narayana Group!",
